---
import MainLayout from '../components/layouts/MainLayout.astro'
import CoherenceVisualizer from '../components/interactive/CoherenceVisualizer.jsx'
---

<MainLayout title="Home">
  <h1>Observer-Centrism</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">A Framework for Physics, Mind, and Structure</p>

  <p>
    A derivation of quantum mechanics, general relativity, thermodynamics,
    the particle spectrum, holography, and the basis of experience
    from three axioms.
  </p>

  <CoherenceVisualizer client:load />
  <p class="viz-caption">
    The minimal observer pair: two phase oscillators with opposite winding
    numbers (+1, &minus;1), exchanging coherence while the total is conserved.
    Each loop closes on itself &mdash; the simplest structure satisfying all
    three axioms.
  </p>

  <div class="axiom-card">
    <h3>Axiom 1: Coherence Conservation</h3>
    <p>
      There exists a primitive quantity &mdash; coherence &mdash; that is globally
      conserved. Coherence cannot be created from nothing, destroyed, or exported
      to an external reservoir. The ontology is closed.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="axiom-card">
    <h3>Axiom 2: The Observer Definition</h3>
    <p>
      Any structure that maintains at least one invariant quantity across
      transformations, together with a distinction between transformations that
      preserve that invariant (self) and those that threaten it (non-self),
      qualifies as an observer.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="axiom-card">
    <h3>Axiom 3: Loop Closure</h3>
    <p>
      Observer dynamics must be closed loops. The internal dynamics of an observer
      must be cyclic: the state must return, at least approximately, to its initial
      configuration after a finite time.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>This Site</h2>
  <p>
    This site houses the ongoing development of Observer-Centrism: rigorous
    derivations from the axioms, exploration of the framework's structure,
    and development of measurable predictions.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="/source/01-introduction">Source Document</a> &mdash; the original framework description</li>
    <li><a href="/derivations/">Derivations</a> &mdash; rigorous proofs and formalizations</li>
    <li><a href="/predictions/">Predictions</a> &mdash; testable consequences unique to this framework</li>
    <li><a href="/postulates">Structural Postulates</a> &mdash; assumptions beyond the three axioms</li>
    <li><a href="/map">Dependency Map</a> &mdash; interactive graph of the derivation chain</li>
    <li><a href="/search">Search</a> &mdash; full-text search across all content</li>
  </ul>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .viz-caption {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
    max-width: 360px;
  }
</style>
